reviews.review_text: why didnt anyone rate this??? playin is long and dreamy and the whole back end of the show kicks total butt. Arnd and Arnd ++ one more saturday, dancin... listen to the crowd. 5 for music and 3.5 for sound.

check it out crazy fingers>comes a times, first set , fuckin awesome, sound could be better i figure some of these 76 shows dont get reviews cuss there are so many good boards from 76.. just to point out 76 has some of the coolest setlist the dead played

Killer show I was there for all 4 nights of this part of the tour, & this one is my favorite. The energy was incredible - check out the uptempo Eyes. We used to call it 'your Eyes on speed'. The Tower sat 3500 & had great acoustics - lots of quality auds from there. This one's a keeper!

loving june just nearing the tail end of june 76 and what a month, this show has a little bit more unorthodox setlist than most of 76 and what a set list it is, this show is just great start to finish. real good quality on the sound too

More 76 Energy I've noticed a lot of these June 76 shows start off with a ton of energy in tunes like TMNS, Cold Rain, Sugaree, and Help>Slip>Frankins. This night was no exception. US Blues and TMNS get the audience in the mood for a Grateful Dead concert right away. Things slow down with beautiful renditions of Crazy Fingers and Comes a Time. Pretty standard material for the remainder of the fist set, featuring a trademark 76 slowed down TLEO, to be compared with the super fast versions from 73. Promised closes off the set, as is becoming routine by this point, a mildly interesting change from its role as a show opener for much of 73.

The second set is really hot. Super cool Playin>Drums>Wheel>Playin sandwich gets the ball rolling. Playing Wheel early in the second set seems to be routine for this era, and I can't get enough of it. Eyes>Dancin has some incredible jams with Jerry going crazy on the guitar solos. Around>GDTRFB>Sat Night carry energy comparable to 72 Sugar Mags and make for a powerful end to a fantastic night of music. So grateful all this music is available on here for those of us who missed the opportunity to see it live to live vicariously through!
